<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
It seems to me that some of the low level staves are almost useless. In particular, consider Staves of Sense Hidden. To fully detect traps on a level you need to cast Sense Hidden probably 10-15 times, depending on the level of the spell and how efficiently you can place your casting positions. This means that your typical staff found on the ground or bought from a shop will last you less than a single level (and it weighs 5 pounds!). <p>
I wonder if it would be in order to allow increase the number of charges, just for certain low level spells. Sense Hidden, Sense Monsters, Disarm, Globe of Light, for example. 
</p>
<p>
On a related note, recharging is not very useful as it stands, I think. When you finally find that high level Staff of Identify which can ID your entire pack or perhaps has the radius effect, you typically can only recharge it two or three times before it explodes: and each recharge just grants a few more charges. 
</p>
<hr>
 <a href="./GregSweetman">GregSweetman</a>: Hmm, tricky one this.  You see, with Staves of Sense Hidden (when I don't have the spell) I only use the charges when I think it is worthwhile (i.e. if I find a vault, or hit a multiplication trap). (Bear in mind that it can be recharged of course) <p>
With regard to recharging exploding everything, I can't say I've noticed, but then I *rarely* use recharging. Perhaps, rather than increasing the number of charges, have the recharging explosion effect tied into the number of charges in the staff vs the staff's spell level?  Or perhaps make a capacity for the staff which can't be exceeded without risk of explosion? 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


